title: U.S. Stock ETFs Retreat on Stimulus Uncertainty
text: U.S. markets and stock exchange traded funds retreated as hopes for an economic stimulus package passing before the November elections begin to fade. On Monday, the Invesco QQQ Trust (NASDAQ: QQQ) dropped 0.6%, SPDR Dow Jones Industrial Average ETF (NYSEArca: DIA) was down 0.6% and iShares Core S&P 500 ETF (NYSEArca: IVV) fell 0.6%.

title: Oil settles with a modest loss as OPEC+ committee meeting fails to prop up prices
text: Oil futures settled a nickel lower on Monday, as a committee meeting of Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries and their allies failed to provide much support for prices. In a statement, the committee reiterated their commitment to the production-cut agreement and said it "encouraged" participating countries to increase efforts to compensate for "overproduced volumes" to rebalance the market.
